Adapter behavior (per F.8 spec):
  ✓ Adapter object: toolkit='airtable',
    events=['AIRTABLE_NEW_RECORD_TRIGGER'].
  ✓ initialState: calls AIRTABLE_LIST_RECORDS with
    sort=[{field:'createdTime',direction:'desc'}],
    maxRecords/pageSize=100, optional view + filterByFormula.
    Persists { last_seen_record_id: <newest_id>,
              last_seen_record_ids: [up to 20 most recent IDs] }.
    Returning null on an empty table.
  ✓ poll: same fetch (no offset pagination — newest records are at
    the top so the first page is all we need). Walks newest→oldest;
    breaks the moment we hit any ID in last_seen_record_ids (ring
    provides robustness against deleted boundary rows).
  ✓ Payload shape: { record, record_id, base_id, table_id, view_id }
    — matches spec literal `{ record, base_id, table_id, view_id }`
    plus a bonus `record_id` convenience field (redundant with
    record.id).
  ✓ Config: accepts both camelCase (baseId/tableId/viewId/
    filterByFormula) AND snake_case (base_id/table_id/view_id/
    filter_by_formula) inputs from Composio trigger_config.
  ✓ Defensive recovery on null lastSeen (empty table or corrupted
    state): silent re-baseline at newest record, zero events. Off-
    by-one acknowledged: first added record on an empty table is
    captured but the EVENT fires on the second poll, not the first.
  ✓ Deleted-boundary fallback: the ring of 20 most recent IDs lets
    the next poll's walk stop at any previously-seen record even
    when the top one was deleted. If the entire ring is gone, the
    adapter emits everything fetched (bounded at FETCH_PAGE_SIZE=
    100 records) as a defensive backfill.
  ✓ Missing baseId / tableId in config throws cleanly so the
    cron-kicker circuit breaker counts it.
  ✓ HTTP errors + successful=false envelope both throw cleanly.

