Adversarial review (review-1.json):
  Opus 4.7 via Agent tool; verdict: ship; 0 blockers; 4 nits.
  Nits:
    - empty-table off-by-one (acknowledged; bounded)
    - no offset pagination (>100 new records per poll would drop
      excess; bounded; could log a warning for observability)
    - bonus record_id field outside spec literal (harmless)
    - view_id: undefined object key when viewId absent (serializes
      away via JSON; harmless)

Notes / decisions:
  - State extension {last_seen_record_id + last_seen_record_ids}
    is backward-compatible: when stored state only has the single
    id, the poll path falls back to a 1-element ring containing
    just that id. Old composio_poll_state rows still work.
  - Walk-newest-and-break-on-known-id is the canonical "new
    records" pattern when the underlying API supports desc sort
    on a stable timestamp. Avoids id-ordering assumptions (Airtable
    record IDs are not sortable lexically).
  - First-page-only fetch is justified by the trigger semantics:
    we only care about records newer than the prior boundary, and
    100 records per cron-kicker minute is well above any realistic
    workspace's data-arrival rate.
  - Composio's response envelope `{ data: { response_data: {
    records, offset? } } }` is consumed, offset is intentionally
    ignored.

